                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/523: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-14T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 14—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>592. For the Secretary. Saw Italian Ambassador to France at anniversary review
                    this morning. In answer to my question he said that in his opinion war in
                    Abyssinia is inevitable; that British Ambassador <pb facs="0718" n="616"
                        xml:id="pg_616"/> here had suggested to Laval a meeting between Mussolini,
                    Laval and Hoare in an endeavor to find a solution that might avoid an armed
                    conflict; that Laval had telephoned to Mussolini, and that Mussolini had replied
                    that discussion would not alter his determination to maintain his position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
